This implementation returns the concatenation of the `_baseURI` and the token-specific uri if the latter is set This enables the following behaviors: - if `_tokenURIs[tokenId]` is set, then the result is the concatenation   of `_baseURI` and `_tokenURIs[tokenId]` (keep in mind that `_baseURI`   is empty per default); - if `_tokenURIs[tokenId]` is NOT set then we fallback to `super.uri()`   which in most cases will contain `ERC1155._uri`; - if `_tokenURIs[tokenId]` is NOT set, and if the parents do not have a   uri value set, then the result is empty.
